  "text": "Li et al. [CITATION_1] also consider in-session tasks. They use query words, query co-occurrence, and the temporal sequence of queries as their main signals. Their learning algorithm is quadratic, but they have a linear approximation which works well in practice. Hua et al. [CITATION_2] showed the importance of semantic features for in-session task identification.",
